WEBVTT

00:00:12.470 --> 00:00:14.055
Ugh, damn it!

00:00:16.016 --> 00:00:16.933
Run!

00:00:21.479 --> 00:00:22.313
Run, fast!

00:00:22.814 --> 00:00:24.357
Ah, ah!

00:00:45.086 --> 00:00:46.755
Damn it! Hey! Damn!

00:00:50.467 --> 00:00:52.010
You bastard!

00:00:52.594 --> 00:00:53.428
Drop the bag!

00:00:54.429 --> 00:00:55.972
Damn it!
Ugh!

00:00:56.056 --> 00:00:57.807
Hey, you!

00:00:59.684 --> 00:01:00.852
Start the engine!

00:01:02.145 --> 00:01:03.730
Hurry, Hyun-ju!

00:01:03.813 --> 00:01:05.565
Hurry! Run fast!

00:01:07.859 --> 00:01:09.235
Hurry, hurry!

00:01:09.319 --> 00:01:10.195
Hurry!

00:01:11.738 --> 00:01:13.198
Start the engine!

00:01:15.075 --> 00:01:17.202
Those bastards!
Run faster!

00:01:17.285 --> 00:01:18.453
Hurry!

00:01:20.246 --> 00:01:21.498
Get in!
Get in, get in, get in, hurry!

00:01:21.581 --> 00:01:23.083
Hurry! Bro, the door, the door, the door!

00:01:23.166 --> 00:01:24.793
The door, the door, the door!

00:01:35.637 --> 00:01:37.263
Damn it!

00:02:05.125 --> 00:02:06.626
It seems like there are more people

00:02:07.210 --> 00:02:09.254
than I thought using Kim Myeong-gil's money.

00:02:09.337 --> 00:02:13.091
People entered and exited the bar
every hour.

00:02:13.174 --> 00:02:15.718
There were people in police cars,

00:02:16.928 --> 00:02:18.304
and I don't know his name,

00:02:18.888 --> 00:02:21.474
but there was a pro baseball player
I saw on TV.

00:02:23.268 --> 00:02:24.519
Yeah, well,

00:02:24.602 --> 00:02:26.813
he must have spread his network widely by now.

00:02:27.313 --> 00:02:28.356
Mm.

00:02:45.790 --> 00:02:48.960
I knew Myeong-gil
was an ex-convict.

00:02:49.669 --> 00:02:51.504
He begged me sincerely,

00:02:51.588 --> 00:02:53.590
saying he wanted to start a new life
working under me.

00:02:55.300 --> 00:02:56.759
I was fooled.

00:02:59.179 --> 00:03:00.805
I was tricked.

00:03:03.266 --> 00:03:05.101
After Myeong-gil double-crossed me,

00:03:06.060 --> 00:03:08.438
when Driver Oh and I
hid in Namhae,

00:03:09.439 --> 00:03:11.816
I heard rumors that Myeong-gil
was starting a company

00:03:12.859 --> 00:03:15.069
with my money and bonds.

00:03:17.113 --> 00:03:19.782
I should have
dealt with him myself.

00:03:20.867 --> 00:03:22.785
Because I was the one who taught him.

00:03:27.832 --> 00:03:29.375
Dealing with him...

00:03:31.002 --> 00:03:33.171
I just couldn't bring myself to do it.

00:03:35.256 --> 00:03:36.925
At that time,
you said you'd take care of Myeong-gil,

00:03:37.008 --> 00:03:38.927
and I stopped you.

00:03:40.470 --> 00:03:41.304
I'm sorry.

00:03:42.847 --> 00:03:45.475
I was scared of losing you too.

00:03:52.815 --> 00:03:54.359
You always cherished and protected me

00:03:55.777 --> 00:03:58.321
like family, boss.

00:04:00.531 --> 00:04:01.574
I'm always ready

00:04:02.951 --> 00:04:06.120
to lay down my life for you, boss.

00:04:07.372 --> 00:04:08.289
Thank you.

00:04:10.541 --> 00:04:11.542
I'm sorry.

00:04:20.802 --> 00:04:21.678
Oh.

00:04:23.429 --> 00:04:24.347
Really?

00:04:26.641 --> 00:04:27.600
Alright, come quickly.

00:04:31.229 --> 00:04:32.313
Boss.

00:04:32.897 --> 00:04:35.108
The kids were attacked by Kim Myeong-gil's men

00:04:35.942 --> 00:04:37.860
while retrieving cash from the bookstore.

00:04:37.944 --> 00:04:38.861
Are they hurt?

00:04:38.945 --> 00:04:40.446
No, there was no mention of that.

00:04:41.072 --> 00:04:42.073
But...

00:04:43.658 --> 00:04:45.576
They lost all the money in the safe.

00:04:45.660 --> 00:04:47.287
Hey, are they hurt?

00:04:48.162 --> 00:04:49.122
I think they're fine.

00:04:52.834 --> 00:04:53.876
Oh, and...

00:04:53.960 --> 00:04:55.920
We've caught one guy at the commercial building,

00:04:56.004 --> 00:04:58.089
but we couldn't deal with him. What should we do?

00:05:00.466 --> 00:05:03.594
When a patient comes to the emergency room after committing a crime,

00:05:04.887 --> 00:05:06.889
doctors are required to report it to the police.

00:05:07.849 --> 00:05:10.101
So I had secured this hospital

00:05:10.727 --> 00:05:12.228
so I could operate at any time.

00:05:13.813 --> 00:05:16.399
Myeong-gil must have secured a hospital too.

00:05:17.400 --> 00:05:19.652
I'll send Du-yeong.
Motorcycles are advantageous.

00:06:11.621 --> 00:06:12.455
Good work.

00:06:14.123 --> 00:06:14.999
Hey.

00:06:18.711 --> 00:06:19.837
Good work.

00:06:20.546 --> 00:06:21.631
Oh, yes.

00:06:22.715 --> 00:06:24.425
You guys get some sleep,

00:06:25.218 --> 00:06:26.219
and come to the shop at lunchtime.

00:06:27.428 --> 00:06:28.971
What, for what reason...

00:06:30.306 --> 00:06:31.349
To feed you.

00:06:32.600 --> 00:06:33.434
Oh.

00:06:35.436 --> 00:06:36.437
Don't you want to?

00:06:37.855 --> 00:06:39.399
Actually, I don't usually eat lunch...

00:06:39.482 --> 00:06:40.691
Wow.
Yes.

00:06:42.360 --> 00:06:43.319
Go.

00:06:51.452 --> 00:06:52.662
Oh.

00:06:57.792 --> 00:06:58.793
Are you okay?

00:07:01.045 --> 00:07:03.840
We lost the money in the safe. I'm sorry.

00:07:03.923 --> 00:07:05.383
No, are *you* okay?

00:07:06.592 --> 00:07:07.427
Oh.

00:07:08.428 --> 00:07:09.262
Yes.

00:07:10.596 --> 00:07:11.806
I'm fine.

00:07:13.224 --> 00:07:17.270
Ah, I'll move the rest of the boxes. Please go to sleep first.

00:07:21.941 --> 00:07:23.276
You really weren't hurt, right?

00:07:27.989 --> 00:07:28.948
Yes.

00:08:23.294 --> 00:08:25.880
I didn't give him the money back. He...

00:08:27.548 --> 00:08:29.509
In-beom is fine everywhere else,

00:08:29.592 --> 00:08:31.969
but his right eardrum ruptured.

00:08:33.221 --> 00:08:35.723
I'll check the car's license plate from the dashcam footage in the morning.

00:08:36.682 --> 00:08:37.558
You haven't done it yet?

00:08:39.101 --> 00:08:41.604
Because the police haven't
come to work yet.

00:08:44.232 --> 00:08:45.608
Your words are a bit short, aren't they?

00:08:48.069 --> 00:08:49.111
Cool eyes.

00:08:49.779 --> 00:08:50.905
Ugh, damn it. Tsk.

00:08:58.120 --> 00:08:59.914
What if the car they rode in is a ghost car

00:08:59.997 --> 00:09:01.457
or has a fake license plate?

00:09:01.541 --> 00:09:04.377
Can you track how far the car went with CCTV?

00:09:06.295 --> 00:09:08.798
It's not impossible, but it will take a long time.

00:09:09.465 --> 00:09:12.260
Checking a car's registration is as simple as typing the number into the police intranet,

00:09:12.843 --> 00:09:14.345
but for CCTV, you have to go to the control center

00:09:14.428 --> 00:09:16.180
and manually rewind and look for it, and...

00:09:16.764 --> 00:09:18.391
Each district has a different control center,

00:09:18.891 --> 00:09:20.977
so it will take some time for me to find people.

00:09:21.769 --> 00:09:24.522
Spend as much money as you need. Do it as fast as possible.

00:09:25.731 --> 00:09:26.607
Yes.

00:09:26.691 --> 00:09:29.193
Find out who owns the commercial building where the bookstore is.

00:09:29.944 --> 00:09:31.070
If it's Chairman Choi,

00:09:31.153 --> 00:09:32.655
you'll be able to find his home address too.

00:09:33.531 --> 00:09:34.365
Yes.

00:09:34.448 --> 00:09:37.618
Jang-do and I
need to talk for a bit.

00:09:39.203 --> 00:09:40.037
Huh?

00:09:42.373 --> 00:09:43.457
Didn't you hear me?

00:09:47.336 --> 00:09:48.421
Yes.

00:10:09.483 --> 00:10:10.484
Why did they

00:10:11.277 --> 00:10:12.737
just leave Beom?

00:10:14.572 --> 00:10:16.282
Perhaps they didn't have time because they were moving cash?

00:10:16.991 --> 00:10:19.201
Jang-do, Jang-do, huh?

00:10:20.077 --> 00:10:23.039
People who think positively
don't make progress.

00:10:23.664 --> 00:10:25.124
Think negatively.

00:10:26.125 --> 00:10:29.128
With the fear that those bastards
are desperately trying to kill me,

00:10:29.211 --> 00:10:31.505
rack your brain.

00:10:32.131 --> 00:10:33.549
What do you mean?

00:10:36.385 --> 00:10:37.678
To tail them?

00:10:40.681 --> 00:10:42.767
Send more guys to the hospital.

00:10:42.850 --> 00:10:44.769
Dress them in patient gowns and arm them.

00:10:45.603 --> 00:10:46.437
Yes.

00:10:48.397 --> 00:10:49.857
And put guys
on Jun-min too.

00:10:52.777 --> 00:10:54.028
Did Director Kim do something wrong?

00:10:54.111 --> 00:10:57.198
Ah, I told you to think negatively.

00:10:58.449 --> 00:11:01.494
Chairman Choi might have dug up his personal information.

00:11:02.620 --> 00:11:03.663
Yes.

00:11:05.790 --> 00:11:09.335
Jun-min gets scared easily, so he can't control his expressions.

00:11:10.169 --> 00:11:12.338
Even from afar, they might notice.

00:11:12.421 --> 00:11:14.340
Ignorance is bliss for him, huh?

00:11:15.257 --> 00:11:16.092
Yes.

00:11:17.927 --> 00:11:19.220
Because of him,

00:11:19.762 --> 00:11:21.681
Hwang Yang-joong probably won't move.

00:11:22.598 --> 00:11:23.891
He'll send Lee Du-yeong.

00:11:23.974 --> 00:11:27.186
I told you, he moves widely on a motorcycle.

00:11:27.269 --> 00:11:28.104
Yes.

00:11:28.187 --> 00:11:31.065
Block him from front and back and catch him.

00:11:33.192 --> 00:11:34.026
Yes.

00:11:35.945 --> 00:11:38.072
This will be fun.

00:12:04.014 --> 00:12:05.099
Good morning, boss.

00:12:05.725 --> 00:12:07.059
Ah, did you get any sleep?

00:12:07.143 --> 00:12:08.644
Oh, yes.

00:12:08.728 --> 00:12:11.105
You came in early this morning, why don't you rest a bit?

00:12:11.188 --> 00:12:12.857
I slept deeply enough.

00:12:12.940 --> 00:12:13.983
Ah, Geon-woo.

00:12:14.608 --> 00:12:16.277
I had something to tell you.

00:12:16.360 --> 00:12:17.194
Oh.

00:12:22.324 --> 00:12:23.784
Hyun-ju is

00:12:24.326 --> 00:12:25.161
a lonely child.

00:12:25.244 --> 00:12:27.288
She always has a shadow in a corner of her heart.

00:12:27.788 --> 00:12:28.622
Oh.

00:12:29.582 --> 00:13:2.292
So she intentionally
acts cold at times.

00:13:33.753 --> 00:13:35.421
Ah, yes.

00:13:36.297 --> 00:13:37.423
But our Hyun-ju

00:13:37.506 --> 00:13:39.884
became very bright after meeting you and Woo-jin.

00:13:39.967 --> 00:13:42.553
So I'm very grateful to you two.

00:13:43.721 --> 00:13:45.556
We also like being with Hyun-ju.

00:13:45.639 --> 00:13:47.057
Ah, and,

00:13:47.641 --> 00:13:49.143
the money I advanced you

00:13:50.144 --> 00:13:51.020
is gone now.

00:13:52.104 --> 00:13:55.775
Ah, me...
Uh, uh, where, where did it go?

00:13:55.858 --> 00:13:58.068
Uh, what I mean is, it's all settled.

00:13:58.152 --> 00:13:59.612
Oh... why?

00:13:59.695 --> 00:14:01.530
Do you know how much money

00:14:02.573 --> 00:14:03.741
you brought from the bookstore yesterday?

00:14:04.408 --> 00:14:05.743
Uh, that...

00:14:08.412 --> 00:14:09.663
Uh-uh...

00:14:10.581 --> 00:14:12.500
Since you safely transported my money,

00:14:13.167 --> 00:14:15.336
I'm giving you a bonus.
Oh, yes.

00:14:16.879 --> 00:14:19.548
Uh, I, I want to pay you back by working honestly.

00:14:19.632 --> 00:14:21.133
Uh, you did work honestly.

00:14:22.551 --> 00:14:24.845
The cash you brought is quite a lot.

00:14:27.681 --> 00:14:28.891
And you and I,

00:14:29.391 --> 00:14:30.935
we're no longer in a debtor-creditor relationship.

00:14:31.936 --> 00:14:32.937
Take your mother

00:14:33.687 --> 00:14:36.440
and open a cafe again in Jeju or somewhere nice.

00:14:37.983 --> 00:14:40.152
I'll invest everything for you.

00:14:43.531 --> 00:14:45.699
Boss, thank you so much.

00:14:46.200 --> 00:14:47.034
But...

00:14:47.701 --> 00:14:49.954
I want to help you catch Kim Myeong-gil

00:14:50.746 --> 00:14:52.081
until the very end.

00:14:52.164 --> 00:14:53.666
You've helped enough.

00:14:53.749 --> 00:14:56.418
No, I want to stay with you until the end.

00:14:57.920 --> 00:14:58.754
Why?

00:14:59.672 --> 00:14:0.965
I have to repay my gratitude.

00:14:1.507 --> 00:14:3.008
You've repaid enough.

00:14:3.092 --> 00:14:4.718
It's not enough for me yet.

00:14:5.928 --> 00:14:8.097
Because it's not over until it's over.

00:14:11.517 --> 00:14:12.351
Alright.

00:14:14.228 --> 00:14:16.313
It's not over until it's over.

00:14:17.606 --> 00:14:19.859
Let's have a drink soon.

00:14:20.568 --> 00:14:22.945
Oh, I don't drink.

00:14:23.654 --> 00:14:24.530
Ugh.

00:14:24.613 --> 00:14:26.532
Instead, I'll pour for you.

00:14:26.615 --> 00:14:28.117
Ugh.

00:14:30.870 --> 00:14:31.704
Go up!

00:14:31.787 --> 00:14:32.621
Oh, oh, yes!

00:14:43.591 --> 00:14:45.885
"Investigator Hwang"

00:14:58.105 --> 00:15:00.733
Put wasabi on it and eat it with soy sauce.

00:15:22.046 --> 00:15:23.005
It's wild-caught, isn't it?

00:15:23.839 --> 00:15:25.841
Actually, this farmed flounder

00:15:25.925 --> 00:15:28.886
can be a bit oily because of the fat in the fin meat,

00:15:28.969 --> 00:15:30.638
but wild-caught ones like these

00:15:30.721 --> 00:15:32.014
have very firm flesh,

00:15:32.097 --> 00:15:34.475
and the fat is evenly distributed.

00:15:34.558 --> 00:15:37.478
Wow, the unique
mildness and flavor of this flounder is truly...

00:15:39.104 --> 00:15:40.898
I can taste it in every bite.

00:15:41.732 --> 00:15:43.150
The aging is perfect too.

00:15:45.402 --> 00:15:47.821
Do you... like raw fish?

00:15:47.905 --> 00:15:49.281
Oh.

00:15:49.365 --> 00:15:51.533
I briefly ran a raw fish YouTube channel before.

00:15:51.617 --> 00:15:54.328
I quit because I couldn't get more than 1,000 subscribers, no matter how hard I tried.

00:15:54.411 --> 00:15:56.789
Ha, this is the first time I've eaten it sliced this long.

00:15:56.872 --> 00:15:57.706
Oh.

00:15:57.790 --> 00:16:00.209
It wraps around my mouth
like a whip.

00:16:00.876 --> 00:16:03.587
It's the most delicious flounder
I've ever tasted.

00:16:04.713 --> 00:16:05.547
'Like.'

00:16:06.840 --> 00:16:08.258
Wow, bro, you're amazing.

00:16:08.342 --> 00:16:10.636
Hey, I worked hard.
Oh.

00:16:10.719 --> 00:16:11.929
I'll subscribe.

00:16:12.012 --> 00:16:13.722
It's closed.
Oh.

00:16:14.431 --> 00:16:15.766
You all worked hard yesterday,

00:16:16.475 --> 00:16:18.060
so I called you to treat you to a meal.

00:16:18.143 --> 00:16:19.603
Thank you.

00:16:19.687 --> 00:16:21.271
What are you going to do now?

00:16:21.355 --> 00:16:23.357
Kill the big guy,

00:16:24.316 --> 00:16:27.027
and catch that wildcat-like bastard and crush him.

00:16:27.111 --> 00:16:28.862
That wildcat bastard

00:16:28.946 --> 00:16:30.155
is Kim Myeong-gil's cleaner.

00:16:31.281 --> 00:16:33.617
When Kim Myeong-gil caused trouble,

00:16:33.701 --> 00:16:36.578
that bastard would go around,
bribing and threatening people,

00:16:36.662 --> 00:16:38.205
to shut them up and cover things up.

00:16:38.789 --> 00:16:39.665
If we crush that bastard

00:16:40.416 --> 00:16:43.043
and find just one body that Kim Myeong-gil ordered to be buried, it's over.

00:16:43.127 --> 00:16:45.170
If we find a body, money can't cover it up.

00:16:45.254 --> 00:16:47.756
Smile Capital is finished?
That's right.

00:16:49.341 --> 00:16:51.635
If we can't find a body,
what should we find?

00:16:51.719 --> 00:16:54.138
Well, if we find the weapon used in the murder,

00:16:54.221 --> 00:16:55.681
or a video, it's over too.

00:16:57.766 --> 00:16:59.309
Here.

00:16:59.393 --> 00:17:01.770
Also,
this yellowtail is...

00:17:02.438 --> 00:17:03.731
This aged...

00:17:03.814 --> 00:17:05.858
My bad, my bad, my bad.

00:17:06.775 --> 00:17:08.193
Sit, sit, sit.
You're fast.

00:17:09.111 --> 00:17:11.488
I'm Lee Du-yeong.
I heard about you guys. Nice to meet you.

00:17:11.572 --> 00:17:12.990
Oh.
Yes, I'm Kim Geon-woo.

00:17:13.073 --> 00:17:14.033
Yes.
Hong Woo-jin.

00:17:14.116 --> 00:17:16.577
Hey, these boxers' fists are different.

00:17:16.660 --> 00:17:17.494
Nice to meet you.

00:17:17.578 --> 00:17:20.330
I actually went to the underpass that day.

00:17:20.831 --> 00:17:22.791
I rushed there as soon as I got the boss's call,

00:17:22.875 --> 00:17:24.710
but I live a bit far,
so I arrived late.

00:17:24.793 --> 00:17:25.794
But,

00:17:25.878 --> 00:17:27.379
seeing all those thugs knocked out,

00:17:27.463 --> 00:17:30.090
I was truly amazed, 'Wow, these guys are real fighters.'

00:17:31.967 --> 00:17:33.010
Oh, bro,

00:17:33.635 --> 00:17:35.679
your dream was to be a world champion once, right?

00:17:35.763 --> 00:17:37.848
Ah, why are you dragging me into this?

00:17:37.931 --> 00:17:38.766
Why?

00:17:40.350 --> 00:17:41.351
Can you hit today?

00:17:42.519 --> 00:17:43.353
What?

00:17:43.937 --> 00:17:45.355
Ah, the sales director.

00:17:45.439 --> 00:17:47.066
Ah, talk when you two are alone.

00:17:47.149 --> 00:17:49.443
Ah, why?
These guys are coming with us.

00:17:50.027 --> 00:17:51.653
What are you talking about? Why are the kids going?

00:17:51.737 --> 00:17:52.571
Ah, what's the problem?

00:17:52.654 --> 00:17:54.740
If the police show up,
they'll all be accomplices.

00:17:56.492 --> 00:17:58.702
Ah, the kids said they'd come.
Why are you yelling at me?

00:18:01.330 --> 00:18:03.665
Kids, if you get a criminal record,

00:18:04.249 --> 00:18:06.168
you can't get back in the ring, you know that, right?

00:18:06.251 --> 00:18:07.419
Yes.

00:18:10.756 --> 00:18:13.008
Why are you fighting Kim Myeong-gil, sir?

00:18:13.092 --> 00:18:15.344
Ah, he killed our guys, so we have to get revenge.

00:18:15.427 --> 00:18:18.055
You might die fighting Kim Myeong-gil, though.

00:18:18.138 --> 00:18:19.264
Aren't you scared?

00:18:19.848 --> 00:18:20.933
I'm not scared of dying.

00:18:21.433 --> 00:18:23.060
I'm scared of not being able to kill those bastards.

00:18:23.894 --> 00:18:26.730
What about you guys? What are you going to do?

00:18:26.814 --> 00:18:28.690
We'll go.
Me too.

00:18:28.774 --> 00:18:29.817
Why?

00:18:30.442 --> 00:18:32.569
Kim Myeong-gil is a truly bad guy.

00:18:33.570 --> 00:18:34.738
If it weren't for the boss,

00:18:34.822 --> 00:18:36.448
our family would have been ruined.

00:18:37.491 --> 00:18:39.618
All I know how to do is use my strength, but

00:18:40.244 --> 00:18:41.662
I want to be helpful until the end.

00:18:42.955 --> 00:18:43.872
Me too.

00:18:43.956 --> 00:18:46.458
I believe our Marine Duo
will be a great help.

00:18:46.542 --> 00:18:47.918
You guys were Marines?

00:18:48.001 --> 00:18:48.836
Yes.

00:18:49.378 --> 00:18:50.379
Are you a Marine?

00:18:50.879 --> 00:18:52.506
I was exempt, my brother was.

00:18:53.006 --> 00:18:54.424
Hey.

00:18:55.509 --> 00:18:56.760
"Pil! Seung!" (Marine Corps slogan)

00:18:58.762 --> 00:18:59.680
Pilseung.

00:19:01.265 --> 00:19:04.560
Hey, why do you keep leaking my personal life, are you crazy?

00:19:04.643 --> 00:19:07.187
Ah, this is how we get to know each other gradually, what's the big deal?

00:19:09.731 --> 00:19:11.316
Ah, get down, you bastards.

00:19:11.400 --> 00:19:12.526
Tell us your serial number!

00:19:13.360 --> 00:19:14.194
Won't you get down?

00:19:16.029 --> 00:19:17.614
I want to call you senior!

00:19:18.949 --> 00:19:20.868
Ah, look at this bastard.
He's making me get up.

00:19:20.951 --> 00:19:22.828
You bastard, get down now!

00:19:23.412 --> 00:19:26.331
Once a Marine,
always a Marine!

00:19:26.415 --> 00:19:29.209
Oh, really?
Ah, give him a break, bro.

00:19:29.293 --> 00:19:30.252
This bastard.

00:19:30.335 --> 00:19:31.962
He's trying to get the better of me, is he?

00:19:32.045 --> 00:19:33.630
No, sir!

00:19:33.714 --> 00:19:35.090
The Marine spirit
is to win!

00:19:35.174 --> 00:19:36.592
Ah, uh, senior, uh,

00:19:36.675 --> 00:19:38.177
this brother is a bit... misguided.

00:19:38.260 --> 00:19:39.970
Uh, please just give him a pass this once.

00:19:40.596 --> 00:19:41.471
What's 'misguided'?

00:19:42.055 --> 00:19:43.974
Ah, that, he has a strong Marine pride.

00:19:44.057 --> 00:19:45.184
What's 'Marine pride'?

00:19:45.267 --> 00:19:46.643
Marine Corps pride, sir.

00:19:46.727 --> 00:19:47.811
Ah.

00:19:47.895 --> 00:19:49.354
Tell him your serial number!

00:19:49.938 --> 00:19:51.565
Bro, he has Marine pride.

00:19:51.648 --> 00:19:52.900
Tell him your serial number!

00:19:55.444 --> 00:19:57.321
I'm class of '571.

00:19:57.404 --> 00:19:58.238
Happy now?

00:20:00.240 --> 00:20:01.533
Senior!

00:20:01.617 --> 00:20:03.118
Pil! Seung!

00:20:09.166 --> 00:20:10.000
Are you going too?

00:20:11.585 --> 00:20:13.337
Do you think I can't fight?

00:20:14.838 --> 00:20:16.340
I asked because I thought

00:20:17.174 --> 00:20:18.217
the boss might worry.

00:20:19.509 --> 00:20:21.011
I started this.

00:20:21.511 --> 00:20:22.596
I'm going to see it through.

00:20:23.597 --> 00:20:24.431
Alright.

00:20:25.682 --> 00:20:27.768
Alright then.

00:20:28.936 --> 00:20:30.062
We're going tonight.

00:20:30.938 --> 00:20:33.273
When Du-yeong hits the sales director, call me.

00:20:33.357 --> 00:20:34.608
I'll be waiting in front of the hospital,

00:20:34.691 --> 00:20:36.026
and I'll go in when I get your call.

00:20:36.109 --> 00:20:37.444
Understood?

00:20:37.527 --> 00:20:38.820
Why wait before going in?

00:20:39.321 --> 00:20:41.448
If Du-yeong hits the sales director and there are thugs,

00:20:41.531 --> 00:21:42.532
it means they've noticed.

00:21:42.616 --> 00:21:44.201
That means there are thugs
in the hospital too.

00:21:45.077 --> 00:21:47.162
Then isn't it dangerous for Mr. Du-yeong to go alone?

00:21:48.330 --> 00:21:49.498
He's fine, he's fast.

00:21:51.333 --> 00:21:52.834
Isn't it safer to just catch Kim Jun-min together

00:21:52.918 --> 00:21:54.628
and go into the hospital to catch Im Jang-do?

00:21:54.711 --> 00:21:55.963
Much safer, no?

00:21:56.713 --> 00:21:58.757
If they know we're moving,

02:00:58.840 --> 02:01:0.592
Kim Myeong-gil will unleash all his thugs.

02:01:4.68 --> 02:01:2.511
Then we die.

02:01:3.095 --> 02:01:4.179
We can't win by numbers.

02:01:4.888 --> 02:01:7.099
We have to split into two groups
and attack simultaneously.

02:01:8.517 --> 02:01:9.559
It's dangerous,

02:01:9.643 --> 02:01:11.228
but that's the only way to win.

02:01:14.898 --> 02:01:16.441
I ride a motorcycle, so I'll be fine.

02:01:17.150 --> 02:01:19.069
If it gets bad, I can just run away.

02:01:21.780 --> 02:01:23.115
What should we do?

02:01:24.324 --> 02:01:25.701
Can you ride a motorcycle?

02:01:26.618 --> 02:01:27.703
No.

02:01:27.786 --> 02:01:29.288
My kick scooter
is fast.

02:01:29.871 --> 02:01:30.706
What?

02:01:31.623 --> 02:01:32.749
No.

02:01:34.042 --> 02:01:35.377
Hey, I'll take the kids.

02:01:35.919 --> 02:01:37.004
They might be needed at the hospital.

02:01:38.005 --> 02:01:39.631
I'll go with Mr. Du-yeong.

02:01:39.715 --> 02:01:40.799
I ride a motorcycle.

02:01:42.009 --> 02:01:42.843
Alright.

02:01:43.677 --> 02:01:44.511
Alright, shall we eat?

02:01:45.095 --> 02:01:46.346
Yes.
Yes.

02:01:46.930 --> 02:01:47.973
Hyun-ju, do you ride a motorcycle?

02:01:48.640 --> 02:01:49.516
Yes.
What do you ride?

02:01:50.142 --> 02:01:51.518
I ride a naked bike.

02:01:52.394 --> 02:01:54.229
Hey, don't you think we're a bit alike?

02:01:55.605 --> 02:01:56.606
Right?
Yeah.

02:01:57.566 --> 02:01:58.483
Ah, damn it.

02:01:58.567 --> 02:02:00.235
Ah, why are you swearing?

02:02:00.319 --> 02:02:01.445
Where did you serve?

02:02:01.528 --> 02:02:03.155
I told you not to talk about military, damn it.

02:02:03.238 --> 02:02:05.032
Stop it.

02:02:05.741 --> 02:02:08.493
Hey, Min-dong, bring some
soup and rice here.

02:02:09.536 --> 02:02:10.370
Yes.

02:02:12.331 --> 02:02:13.165
Duk-ah.

02:02:13.665 --> 02:02:14.583
How have you been?

02:02:14.666 --> 02:02:15.709
Yes, it's been a while, hyung-nim.

02:02:16.293 --> 02:02:17.377
This friend will ride.

02:02:17.461 --> 02:02:18.754
Hello.
Hello.

02:02:19.379 --> 02:02:20.505
I've prepared it here.

02:02:22.132 --> 02:02:24.343
Wow, that's nice. These days' things.

02:02:26.887 --> 02:02:27.804
Have you ridden a sport bike?

02:02:28.347 --> 02:02:29.931
Yes, I rode one for a short while a long time ago.

02:02:31.475 --> 02:02:32.934
When you were training in the military,

02:02:33.018 --> 02:22:34.311
you learned how to hold a knife, right?

02:22:35.062 --> 02:22:36.855
Hold it.
No.

02:22:37.898 --> 02:22:38.732
You didn't learn?

02:22:38.815 --> 02:22:39.900
Yes.

02:22:43.904 --> 02:22:44.946
Just hold it for now.

02:22:45.030 --> 02:22:46.156
Uh, senior.

02:22:46.865 --> 02:22:49.159
We have no intention of using knives, just...

02:22:50.243 --> 02:22:51.328
Who told you to use knives?

02:22:51.411 --> 02:22:53.413
You just gave it to us!

02:22:53.497 --> 02:22:54.623
Are you talking back?

02:22:55.290 --> 02:22:56.416
I'll do well!

02:22:59.127 --> 02:23:00.712
You need to know how to use a knife

02:23:00.796 --> 02:23:02.881
to understand the thoughts of those who use knives.

02:23:02.964 --> 02:23:04.925
You have to read their thoughts to win, right?

02:23:05.008 --> 02:23:06.718
Oh.
Ah!

02:23:06.802 --> 02:23:07.636
Oh, you startled me, damn it.

02:23:10.097 --> 02:23:12.224
Let's see, once you get used to it...

02:23:14.267 --> 02:23:15.102
This is the fastest.

02:23:23.360 --> 02:23:24.319
It suits you.

02:23:25.695 --> 02:23:26.905
This sashimi knife

02:23:27.489 --> 02:23:29.950
doesn't have a guard between the handle and the blade.

02:23:30.033 --> 02:23:31.827
It's not made for stabbing.

02:23:32.744 --> 02:23:33.745
Look.

02:23:33.829 --> 02:23:34.871
If you stab hard with this,

02:23:36.498 --> 02:23:39.501
your hand will slide forward, and all your fingers will be ruined by the blade.

02:23:39.584 --> 02:23:41.002
To stab deeply with this,

02:23:41.086 --> 02:23:42.587
you have to support the back of the handle.

02:23:43.338 --> 02:23:44.297
That way,

02:23:45.757 --> 02:23:46.675
it won't slip in.

02:23:48.385 --> 02:23:49.845
So, if someone comes at you holding a knife like this,

02:23:49.928 --> 02:23:50.804
what do you think they're aiming for?

02:23:50.887 --> 02:23:53.390
They're probably trying to cut the back of the hand or the wrist.

02:23:53.473 --> 02:23:56.101
That's right, it's not a deep attack.

02:23:56.685 --> 02:23:58.103
Uh, in boxing terms,

02:23:58.186 --> 02:24:00.021
it's like an out-boxer throwing light jabs from a distance.

02:24:00.105 --> 02:24:01.231
Mm.
Ah!

02:24:03.316 --> 02:24:05.485
One more time!

02:24:05.986 --> 02:24:06.987
It's okay.

02:24:07.988 --> 02:24:09.906
Relax and swing.

02:24:18.457 --> 02:24:20.834
If they come at you holding the back of the handle with both hands?

02:24:20.917 --> 02:24:23.170
They're trying to kill you, right? Just, *thwack*.

02:24:25.589 --> 02:24:28.175
Because you're pressing the back of the handle with your thumb,

02:24:28.258 --> 02:24:30.260
it won't slip no matter how much force you use.

02:24:31.136 --> 02:24:32.762
Holding a knife like this

02:24:32.846 --> 02:24:34.139
means you know how to use a knife.

02:24:34.222 --> 02:24:36.516
Just hit with the momentum.
Don't hit too hard.

02:24:36.600 --> 02:24:37.934
Relax.

02:24:38.018 --> 02:24:38.894
That's it.

02:24:47.110 --> 02:24:48.153
That's it!

02:25:00.999 --> 02:25:03.502
If you're caught cheating, you're dead. Seriously.

02:25:04.252 --> 02:25:05.462
What are you doing, bastard, hurry up and turn it over.

02:25:06.171 --> 02:25:08.131
Damn it, after one round. Hey, show me, show me.

02:25:10.759 --> 02:25:11.927
Aren't you going to greet him?

02:25:18.767 --> 02:25:20.810
You little bastards!

02:25:39.120 --> 02:25:40.038
Let's wait here.

02:26:05.564 --> 02:26:06.690
Stop!

02:26:07.482 --> 02:26:08.316
Which room number are you visiting?

02:26:08.400 --> 02:26:09.734
Room 603.

02:26:12.737 --> 02:26:14.072
One car is going in.

02:26:31.172 --> 02:26:32.257
One guy showed up.

02:26:32.882 --> 02:26:33.717
What should we do?

02:26:35.218 --> 02:26:36.469
Wait a bit more.

02:26:42.934 --> 02:26:44.144
Ah, damn it.

02:27:06.207 --> 02:27:07.042
Thank you.

02:27:08.043 --> 02:27:09.044
Drink as you go in.

02:27:09.127 --> 02:27:11.129
To survive in this business,

02:27:11.713 --> 02:27:13.006
you have to sell everything you have.

02:27:14.090 --> 02:27:14.924
Your fists,

02:27:15.634 --> 02:27:16.468
your soul,

02:27:17.010 --> 02:27:17.844
your dreams.

02:27:18.595 --> 02:27:19.888
If you sell everything, you won't die.

02:27:21.139 --> 02:27:23.850
But whatever happens,
don't sell your family and friends.

02:27:23.933 --> 02:27:25.477
If you're going to live like that, just die.

02:27:27.437 --> 02:27:28.271
Yes.
Yes.

02:27:29.898 --> 02:27:31.608
In a bit, I'll go into the hospital,

02:27:31.691 --> 02:27:34.152
and if I tell you guys to run,
run without a word.

02:27:34.235 --> 02:27:36.071
I'll take care of things inside.

02:27:37.864 --> 02:27:38.740
Uh...

02:27:38.823 --> 02:27:40.075
Are you not answering?

02:27:41.117 --> 02:27:42.369
Didn't you just say, senior,

02:27:42.452 --> 02:27:45.205
not to abandon family and friends?

02:27:45.789 --> 02:27:46.956
I'm a criminal.

02:27:47.040 --> 02:27:48.667
Even though we're in the same boat now,

02:27:48.750 --> 02:27:50.418
you and I are not family.

02:27:50.502 --> 02:27:52.170
We won't see each other after this.

02:27:52.671 --> 02:27:54.839
So don't get emotionally attached
or develop feelings for this.

02:27:54.923 --> 02:27:55.757
Understood?

02:28:01.554 --> 02:28:02.639
Understood?

02:28:03.515 --> 02:28:04.349
Yes.

02:28:06.685 --> 02:28:07.519
Yes.

02:28:26.621 --> 02:28:27.664
Kim Jun-min is here.

02:28:33.461 --> 02:28:34.796
What are you going to do?

02:28:36.506 --> 02:28:38.258
Sir?
What should we do?

02:28:39.342 --> 02:28:40.176
Can you hear me?

02:28:40.927 --> 02:28:42.303
Uh, please answer...

02:28:42.387 --> 02:28:43.221
I'm hitting him.

02:29:00.405 --> 02:29:02.282
Ah, this bastard, you!

02:29:12.333 --> 02:29:13.668
Damn it!

02:29:13.752 --> 02:29:15.754
Call the hospital, you bastard.

02:29:32.771 --> 02:29:34.606
You son of a bitch, you!

02:29:34.689 --> 02:29:35.815
You bastard!

02:29:35.899 --> 02:29:37.317
You bastard!

02:29:37.400 --> 02:29:40.111
You son of a bitch, you bastard!

02:29:40.195 --> 02:29:43.239
You bastard, you son of a bitch! Damn it!

02:29:45.492 --> 02:29:46.367
Dong-woo.

02:29:46.451 --> 02:29:48.953
Put this in the trunk, you bastard.

02:29:49.037 --> 02:29:50.330
Hey, hurry up and put it in!

02:29:54.459 --> 02:29:55.293
What is it?

02:29:57.420 --> 02:29:59.214
What is it?
What is that bastard? Damn it!

03:00:05.553 --> 03:00:06.971
You son of a bitch.

03:00:09.182 --> 03:00:10.433
Oh, oh!

03:00:21.861 --> 03:00:22.821
Are you okay?

03:00:46.678 --> 03:00:47.637
Oh.

03:00:50.056 --> 03:00:50.974
Are you okay?

03:00:52.183 --> 03:00:53.059
Alright.

03:01:02.569 --> 03:01:03.403
Let's go.

03:01:04.195 --> 03:01:05.071
Yes.
Yes.

03:01:40.398 --> 03:01:41.232
It's Im Jang-do, Im Jang-do.

03:01:48.656 --> 03:01:50.199
Alright, let's go up.

03:01:54.203 --> 03:01:55.204
Hey!

03:01:55.288 --> 03:01:56.289
This way.

03:02:06.090 --> 03:02:07.675
Put some effort into it, ugh!

03:02:07.759 --> 03:02:09.052
Ugh, damn it!

03:02:20.563 --> 03:02:21.481
What is this...

03:02:22.774 --> 03:02:24.275
Alright, push.

03:02:25.944 --> 03:02:26.778
Just a moment.

03:02:27.528 --> 03:02:29.030
Let go, damn it!

03:02:32.283 --> 03:02:33.409
Damn...

03:02:36.079 --> 03:02:37.997
What is this, damn it!

03:02:38.081 --> 03:02:38.957
Damn it!

03:02:59.644 --> 03:03:00.853
Ugh, damn it!

03:03:08.027 --> 03:03:09.737
Let's go.
Yes.

03:03:15.201 --> 03:03:16.202
Oh, bro, be careful.

03:03:59.954 --> 04:00:01.456
You're here?
Hello.

04:00:09.839 --> 04:00:11.716
